# YouTube Analytics & Growth Engine

## Introduction

The YouTube Analytics & Growth Engine is an agent designed to help creators analyze their channel performance, predict growth, and optimize revenue streams. It leverages the YouTube Data API to fetch channel metrics, which are then passed to the `Lux.Agents.YouTubeAnalytics` agent for analysis.

## Setup

First, ensure you have set up your YouTube Data API Key and OpenAI API key in your configuration:

```elixir
# In your config.exs or secrets configuration
config :lux, :api_keys,
  youtube: "YOUR_YOUTUBE_API_KEY",
  openai: "YOUR_OPENAI_API_KEY"
```

## Creating the Agent

We can create an instance of the YouTube Analytics agent.

```elixir
alias Lux.Agents.YouTubeAnalytics

{:ok, agent_pid} = YouTubeAnalytics.start_link(%{
  llm_config: %{
    model: "gpt-4o",
    temperature: 0.7
  }
})
```

## Collecting Data

We can use `Lux.Lenses.YouTube.GetChannelInfo` to collect channel metrics.

```elixir
alias Lux.Lenses.YouTube.GetChannelInfo

{:ok, channel_data} = GetChannelInfo.focus(%{
  id: "UC_x5XG1OV2P6uZZ5FSM9Ttw" # Example channel ID
})
```

## Generating the Growth and Revenue Report

Pass the collected metrics into our agent to receive an automated analysis report containing growth prediction, revenue optimization strategies, retention analysis, and a step-by-step action plan.

```elixir
{:ok, report} = YouTubeAnalytics.generate_report(agent_pid, channel_data)

IO.inspect(report.growth_prediction, label: "Growth Prediction")
IO.inspect(report.revenue_optimization, label: "Revenue Optimization")
IO.inspect(report.action_plan, label: "Action Plan")
```
